    {
        "role": "user",
        "text": "Can you compute a value score for NYC listings that combines reviews and availability relative to price ? I'd like to see how listings compare.",
        "created_at": "2026-01-09 15:09:54.371651+00"
    },
    {
        "role": "bot",
        "text": "<p>I derived a custom <span class=\"highlight_field\">value_score</span> for each NYC listing by combining <span class=\"highlight_field\">reviews_per_month</span> and <span class=\"highlight_field\">availability_365</span> relative to <span class=\"highlight_field\">price</span>. Listings with a price of zero were excluded, leaving <strong>42,729 rows</strong>. I also created a <span class=\"highlight_field\">price_tier</span> classification (Budget, Mid-Range, Premium, Luxury).</p><p>Your <span class=\"highlight_mark\">scatter plot</span> places <span class=\"highlight_field\">price</span> on the <span class=\"highlight_channels\">x-axis</span> and <span class=\"highlight_field\">value_score</span> on the <span class=\"highlight_channels\">y-axis</span>, with <span class=\"highlight_channels\">color</span> representing <span class=\"highlight_field\">price_tier</span>. Higher points indicate better value relative to price.</p><button class=\"viz-thumbnail-btn\" data-viz-config=\"{&quot;file&quot;: &quot;specificationsEnhanced_20260109_151004.xml&quot;}\" onclick=\"window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('loadVizFile', {detail: JSON.parse(this.dataset.vizConfig || '{}')}));\"><img src=\"/server/rooms/GUEST_ROOM_TOKEN/artifacts/specificationsEnhanced_20260109_151004.png\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"\" class=\"viz-thumbnail\" /></button><div style=\"margin: 6px 0 10px; display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 5px; font-size: 0.73rem; line-height: 1.6;\"><span style=\"background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); border-radius: 20px; padding: 2px 9px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);\">42,729 pts</span><span style=\"background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); border-radius: 20px; padding: 2px 9px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);\">price: $10 \u2013 $2,000</span><span style=\"background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); border-radius: 20px; padding: 2px 9px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);\">value_score: 0 \u2013 148.7</span><span style=\"background: rgba(27,144,186,0.1); border: 1px solid rgba(27,144,186,0.2); border-radius: 20px; padding: 2px 9px; color: #7ecce8;\">Mid-Range: 50.0% of listings</span><span style=\"background: rgba(220,150,80,0.12); border: 1px solid rgba(220,150,80,0.25); border-radius: 20px; padding: 2px 9px; color: #e8b96a;\">price \u00d7 value_score: r\u202f=\u202f\u22120.13 (weak negative)</span></div><p>The weak negative correlation (r\u202f=\u202f\u22120.13) confirms that price alone is a poor predictor of value \u2014 the highest scores concentrate in the Budget and Mid-Range tiers rather than Premium or Luxury. What would you like to explore next?</p><div class=\"history-anchor\"><button class=\"history-show-viz\" data-tooltip=\"Show visualization\" aria-label=\"Show visualization\" data-viz-config=\"{&quot;file&quot;: &quot;specificationsEnhanced_20260109_151004.xml&quot;}\" onclick=\"window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('loadVizFile', {detail: JSON.parse(this.dataset.vizConfig || '{}')}));\"><img src=\"/icons/viz.svg\" alt=\"\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"height: 1.2em; width: 1.2em; vertical-align: middle;\" /></button><button class=\"history-export-dashboard\" data-tooltip=\"Export to dashboard\" aria-label=\"Export to dashboard\" onclick=\"window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('openExportModal'));\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"height: 1.2em; width: 1.2em; vertical-align: middle; fill: white; opacity: 0.8;\"><path d=\"M3 13h8V3H3v10zm0 8h8v-6H3v6zm10 0h8V11h-8v10zm0-18v6h8V3h-8z\"/></svg></button></div>",
