    {
        "role": "user",
        "text": "Can you show me the room availability across the year by minimum_nights and by the price ? Keep only the rows where minimum_nights is less than 300. Use a 3D surface for that and color by price using a SPECTRAL color palette. Put the price on the Z axis.",
        "created_at": "2026-01-09 15:13:55.870657+00"
    },
    {
        "role": "bot",
        "text": "<p>I filtered out listings with <span class=\"highlight_field\">minimum_nights</span> of 300 or more, keeping <strong>229,825 rows</strong>. Then I generated a <span class=\"highlight_mark\">3D surface</span> visualization.</p><p>The <span class=\"highlight_channels\">x-axis</span> represents <span class=\"highlight_field\">availability_365</span>, the <span class=\"highlight_channels\">y-axis</span> shows <span class=\"highlight_field\">minimum_nights</span>, and the <span class=\"highlight_channels\">z-axis</span> encodes <span class=\"highlight_field\">price</span>. The surface is colored by <span class=\"highlight_field\">price</span> using the Spectral palette, revealing how pricing varies across these two dimensions.</p><button class=\"viz-thumbnail-btn\" data-viz-config=\"{&quot;file&quot;: &quot;specificationsEnhanced_20260109_151406.xml&quot;}\" onclick=\"window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('loadVizFile', {detail: JSON.parse(this.dataset.vizConfig || '{}')}));\"><img src=\"/server/rooms/GUEST_ROOM_TOKEN/artifacts/specificationsEnhanced_20260109_151406.png\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"\" class=\"viz-thumbnail\" /></button><div style=\"margin: 6px 0 10px; display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 5px; font-size: 0.73rem; line-height: 1.6;\"><span style=\"background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); border-radius: 20px; padding: 2px 9px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);\">229,825 pts</span><span style=\"background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); border-radius: 20px; padding: 2px 9px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);\">availability_365: 0 \u2013 365</span><span style=\"background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); border-radius: 20px; padding: 2px 9px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);\">minimum_nights: 1 \u2013 299</span><span style=\"background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); border-radius: 20px; padding: 2px 9px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);\">price: $0 \u2013 $2,000</span><span style=\"background: rgba(220,150,80,0.12); border: 1px solid rgba(220,150,80,0.25); border-radius: 20px; padding: 2px 9px; color: #e8b96a;\">r(min_nights, price)\u202f=\u202f\u22120.13</span></div><p>Listings with longer minimum stay requirements trend slightly cheaper (r\u202f=\u202f\u22120.13 between <span class=\"highlight_field\">minimum_nights</span> and <span class=\"highlight_field\">price</span>), while year-round availability has almost no linear relationship with price (r\u202f=\u202f0.07). Is there anything else you\u2019d like to visualize?</p><div class=\"history-anchor\"><button class=\"history-show-viz\" data-tooltip=\"Show visualization\" aria-label=\"Show visualization\" data-viz-config=\"{&quot;file&quot;: &quot;specificationsEnhanced_20260109_151406.xml&quot;}\" onclick=\"window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('loadVizFile', {detail: JSON.parse(this.dataset.vizConfig || '{}')}));\"><img src=\"/icons/viz.svg\" alt=\"\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"height: 1.2em; width: 1.2em; vertical-align: middle;\" /></button><button class=\"history-export-dashboard\" data-tooltip=\"Export to dashboard\" aria-label=\"Export to dashboard\" onclick=\"window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('openExportModal'));\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"height: 1.2em; width: 1.2em; vertical-align: middle; fill: white; opacity: 0.8;\"><path d=\"M3 13h8V3H3v10zm0 8h8v-6H3v6zm10 0h8V11h-8v10zm0-18v6h8V3h-8z\"/></svg></button></div>",
